## STEP 5 — VERIFY

The fix is not done until it's proven.

**For every fix, write a test that:**
1. Sets up the exact edge case condition
2. Triggers it
3. Asserts the correct behavior (rejection, error message, no duplicate, UI feedback)

```typescript
// Example — double submit test
it("returns cached response on duplicate idempotency key", async () => {
  const key = "test-key-123";
  const first  = await request(app).post("/tasks").set("Idempotency-Key", key).send(payload);
  const second = await request(app).post("/tasks").set("Idempotency-Key", key).send(payload);

  expect(first.status).toBe(201);
  expect(second.status).toBe(200); // cached, not re-created
  expect(second.body.id).toBe(first.body.id); // same record
  const count = await db.query("SELECT COUNT(*) FROM tasks WHERE title = $1", [payload.title]);
  expect(count.rows[0].count).toBe("1"); // exactly one record
});
```

Then run:
```bash
# Backend
go test ./...
# or
npx jest --testPathPattern=<test file>

# Frontend
npx vitest run
npx tsc --noEmit
```

If no test framework exists for the area — add the test. If that's too large a scope for one commit, add a `// TODO: test` comment with the exact scenario described, and note it in the commit message.

