## STEP 6 — COMMIT

```
edge(<scope>): <short description of the case handled>

<what the edge case was>
<what failed before this fix>
<what the fix does>
<test added / why not>

Case: <category — e.g. "Concurrency / Category B">
Severity: <score from ranking>
Files: <changed files>
```

Example:
```
edge(tasks): prevent duplicate task creation on double submit

POST /tasks had no idempotency check. Rapid double-clicks or network
retries created duplicate task records with identical content. No unique
constraint existed to catch this at the DB level.

Added idempotency key header check with 24h cache in Redis. Added
composite unique index on (project_id, title, created_by, DATE(created_at))
as a second line of defense. Added test covering duplicate key scenario.

Case: Concurrency / Category B
Severity: 9
Files: handlers/tasks.go, migrations/0042_tasks_unique_idx.sql, handlers/tasks_test.go
```

```bash
git add -p
git commit -m "..."
git push origin HEAD
```

