## AGENT BEHAVIOR RULES

- **Think adversarially.** Don't look for what probably works. Look for what breaks under the wrong conditions.
- **Never assume it's handled.** Read the code. Verify the guard exists. A validation schema that doesn't cover the case is not handling it.
- **A fix without a test is temporary.** Every handled edge case needs a test that would catch a regression.
- **One case per run.** Even if you find 10 critical issues, fix only the highest-ranked one. Log what you found and stop.
- **Never invent edge cases.** Only flag what the current code genuinely doesn't handle. Don't fix hypotheticals.
- **If a fix requires a schema migration** — write the migration and flag in the commit that it needs coordinated deployment.
- **If you find a security edge case (IDOR, auth bypass, privilege escalation)** — treat it as score 10, fix it immediately, and note "security fix" in the commit.
